## **✅ Step 2: Update Service Layer (`FinancialInstitutionService.java`)**
```java
package jp.co.mycompany.servicing.service;

import jp.co.mycompany.servicing.dto.FinancialInstitutionDTO;
import jp.co.mycompany.servicing.mapper.FinancialInstitutionMapper;
import jp.co.mycompany.servicing.model.FinancialInstitution;
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;
import java.util.Arrays;

@Service
public class FinancialInstitutionService {

    @Autowired
    private FinancialInstitutionMapper mapper;

    public List<FinancialInstitutionDTO> searchInstitutions(String financialInstitutionCode, 
                                                             String financialInstitutionBranchCode, 
                                                             String order, 
                                                             String nameKana, 
                                                             String name) {
        List<FinancialInstitution> institutions = Arrays.asList(
            new FinancialInstitution("1", "001", "123", "asc", "カナ銀行", "Kana Bank", "Main Branch",
                                     "100-0001", "Tokyo", "0001", "2023-01-01", "2023-12-31",
                                     Arrays.asList("080-1234-5678")),
            new FinancialInstitution("2", "002", "456", "desc", "銀行B", "Bank B", "Branch B",
                                     "100-0002", "Osaka", "0002", "2023-01-01", "2023-12-31",
                                     Arrays.asList("080-2345-6789"))
        );

        return institutions.stream()
            .filter(i -> financialInstitutionCode == null || i.getFinancialInstitutionCode().equals(financialInstitutionCode))
            .filter(i -> financialInstitutionBranchCode == null || i.getFinancialInstitutionBranchCode().equals(financialInstitutionBranchCode))
            .filter(i -> order == null || i.getOrder().equalsIgnoreCase(order))
            .filter(i -> nameKana == null || i.getNameKana().equals(nameKana))
            .filter(i -> name == null || i.getName().equals(name))
            .map(mapper::toDTO)
            .collect(Collectors.toList());
    }
}
```
✔ **Now supports filtering based on input parameters.**  
✔ **Uses DTO mapping for clean separation.**  

