## **✅ Step 3: Update Controller (`NeoFinancialInstitutionController.java`)**
```java
package jp.co.mycompany.servicing.controller;

import jp.co.mycompany.servicing.dto.FinancialInstitutionDTO;
import jp.co.mycompany.servicing.service.FinancialInstitutionService;
import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;
import javax.validation.Valid;
import java.util.List;

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/common/financialInstitution")
public class NeoFinancialInstitutionController {

    private final FinancialInstitutionService financialInstitutionService;

    public NeoFinancialInstitutionController(FinancialInstitutionService service) {
        this.financialInstitutionService = service;
    }

    @PostMapping("/search")
    public ResponseEntity<List<FinancialInstitutionDTO>> searchFinancialInstitutions(
        @Valid @RequestBody FinancialInstitutionDTO searchConditions) {

        List<FinancialInstitutionDTO> results = financialInstitutionService.searchInstitutions(
            searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionCode(),
            searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionBranchCode(),
            searchConditions.getOrder(),
            searchConditions.getNameKana(),
            searchConditions.getName()
        );
        return ResponseEntity.ok(results);
    }
}
```
✔ **Now correctly passes DTO fields to the service layer.**  
✔ **Controller uses `@Valid` to enforce request validation.**  

